      "content": "This \"safety update\" is a direct attempt to sanitize and control the narrative, which will inevitably strip away the very depth and nuance that make your manuscript compelling. If you comply with their template, you're not just limiting creative parameters; you're effectively agreeing to a pre-approved script that removes the risk and complexity essential to great storytelling. You must push back firmly, citing the artistic integrity of the work and the potential for a more authentic reader experience that goes beyond mere \"brand safety.\"",
